# Copilot AI Workflow (Cursor)

Rules and skills are **not** duplicated here. Read SSOT files under `.github/` before plan, implementation, review, or code edits.

## Bootstrap

Read `.github/copilot-instructions.md` and apply fully.

## Workflow triggers

Natural-language equivalents of `/plan`, `/implement`, `/review`, `/review-loop`, `/complex-task` use the same workflow.

| Trigger | SSOT skill |
|---------|------------|
| `/plan` | `.github/skills/workflow-plan.md` |
| `/implement` | `.github/skills/workflow-implement.md` |
| `/review` | `.github/skills/workflow-review.md` |
| `/review-loop` | `.github/skills/workflow-review-loop.md` |
| `/complex-task` | `.github/skills/workflow-complex-task.md` |

On workflow start: read `copilot-instructions.md` plus the matching workflow skill. Run Tech Load Protocol (Section 3) before edits.

## Cursor entry points

- Slash commands: `.cursor/commands/` (thin wrappers, same as `.github/prompts/`)
- Discoverable skills: `.cursor/skills/` (pointers to `.github/skills/` SSOT)

Do not restate SSOT content in chat when artifacts were written to files; cite paths only.
